What is the greatest common factor of $518$ and $294$?
inference:
First, find the prime factorization of each number:
$$
\begin{align*}
518&=2\cdot7\cdot37\\
294&=2\cdot3\cdot7^2
\end{align*}
$$
The greatest common factor is the product of the common prime factors, each raised to the smallest power that appears in either factorization:
$$
\text{GCF}(518,294)=2\cdot7=\boxed28$$
Final Answer: $\boxed{28}$. I hope it is correct.
ground_truth: Factoring both numbers, we find that $518=2\cdot 7\cdot 37$ and $294=2\cdot 3\cdot 7^2$. Taking the lowest common powers of both, we see that the greatest common factor of the two numbers is $2\cdot 7=\boxed{14}$.
